fix._preContent:
Remove any accessories needed to access water pump. (in some cases timing belt will need to be removed) Remove water pump bolts and old water pump. Clean water pump mounting services, install new gasket, and new water pump. Reinstall all accessories removed earlier, fill cooling system with manufacturer approved coolant, and retest for leaks. Test drive vehicle

This fix should be performed immediately. More details and shops performing this fix in your area can be found here.

AutoTechIQ's records show that a hot tar or burning oil smell appears across all makes and models.

The burning oil smell varies depending on its cause. The reason can be oil dripping on the exhaust system or leaks in the oil filter and Engine oil pan.

Moreover, sludge build-up or improper procedures from a prior service can lead to an intense burnt rubber, burnt carpet, or burning oil smell.
